      "Text": "graphite2 security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for graphite2 is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Graphite is a system that can be used to create “smart fonts” capable of displaying writing systems with various complex behaviors. A smart font contains not only letter shapes but also additional instructions indicating how to combine and position the letters in complex ways.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nGraphite before 1.3.15 has an integer underflow and resultant out-of-bounds write via Graphite actions, because slotat does not ensure that an offset is within the allowed slot-map range.(CVE-2026-50593)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for graphite2 is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "graphite2",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
